 and one in French by Jean Hotman, show us how De officio pii viri was adapted to the ongoing struggle for church peace in different parts of Europe, a struggle that was led by jurists and theologians, outstanding members of the Republic of Letters, who were able to spread their ideas by their large epistolary networks. The life story of De officio pii viri highlights the birth, expansion and failure of ideas; how they profit from the support of the mighty and how they fail when opposed by the uncompromising: those who think they speak in the name of God.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aChristian unionxHistoryx16th century. 0aChristian unionxHistoryy16th century. 0aChurch historyx16th century. 0aChurch historyy16th century. 4a16. Jahrhundert. 4aHumanismus. 4aIrenik. 4aReformation. 4aReligionsgespräch von Poissy. 7aRELIGION / Christian Theology / History.2bisacsh  a16th-century irenicism.  acolloquy at Poissy.  ahumanism.  areformation.1 aPosthumus Meyjes, Guillaume H. M., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSchoor, Rob van de, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2016 Part 1z978311076250108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2016z978311070100508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2016z9783110485103oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theology, Relig. Studies, Jewish Studies 2016z9783110485394oZDB-23-DGF0 cprintz978311048198340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311048531840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110485318423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110485318/original  a978-3-11-070100-5  DG Plus eBook-Pac